On Friday, October 03, 2003, at 01:29PM, scott lyons <slyons(-at-)netrover.com> wrote:

>2 or 3 bushings depends on the year of the bus. busboys website has the
>details on the cutoff, i think, but i am almost certain 78 has 3 total.

The bus boys site is confusing; I wish they'd fix it.

There are two bushings on the rear shift rod and three (1 forward, 1 middle, 1 rear) on 77 and later models. The middle and rear bushing are the same part number and there was a tech bulletin about modifying all shift rods to this configuration for better shifting.

